{
  "text": "Phylogenetic analysis demonstrated affiliation of strain SEBR 3139T with representatives of the genus Desulfotomaculum. The tree topology (Fig. 3) shows that strains affiliated to the genus Desulfotomaculum are rather diverse, and some of them are not closely related. As previously observed [CITATION_1] , this genus is phylogenetically and physiologically diversified and would probably be reorganized. However, according to our present knowledge concerning metabolic and physiological characteristics and phylogenetic relationships, strain SEBR 3139T can be considered as a member of the genus Desulfotomaculum. This strain is sufficiently different from other members of the genus to be classified as a representative of a new species. We propose the name Desulfotomaculum halophilum sp. nov.",
  "citation_candidates": [
